          <h1 style="color:#004C45;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin:0;text-align: left;"> A Message from Cal Poly Humboldt </h1>
          <p id="date" style="color:#004C45;font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;margin:10px 0 20px 0;text-align: left;"> March 22, 2024</p>
          <p style="color:#004C45;font-size:22px;font-weight:bold;margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:28px">Plans for the Summer 2024 Term</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-color="#F2A900" padding="0" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="light-wrap" padding-bottom="20px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text>Dear Students,
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text>I hope you are returning energized from Spring Break. I am excited to share with you the plans for the Summer 2024 academic session.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>I know that undergraduates who enroll in a summer term are better able to manage their course loads, are more likely to graduate on time, and can register in unique academic opportunities like field studies courses and faculty-led study abroad. The University wants to support your ability to take advantage of these summer course and program opportunities.</mj-text>

          <mj-text><strong>This summer, when you enroll and stay in six units, the University will cover the tuition costs for
            up to four of those units</strong>. If you already qualify for financial aid, you may get more units covered. If you
            enroll in a field studies or faculty-led study abroad program, scholarships are available to help with those
            costs, too.
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text>The Summer 2024 course schedule will go live on the <a href="https://registrar.humboldt.edu/summer-term">Office of the Registrarâ€™s website</a> on March 22, 2024 and all continuing students can begin registering for the summer on April 8, 2024. </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0">Summer 2024 session dates are:</mj-text>
        <mj-text padding-top="0">
          <ul>
            <li>Full 8-week Session: May 28 to July 19</li>
            <li>First 5-week Session: May 28 to June 28</li>
            <li>Second 5-week Session: July 1 to August 2</li>
          </ul>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text>To plan your courses, please reach out to your designated academic advisor. More information about Summer financial aid programs can be found on the <a href="https://finaid.humboldt.edu/apply-for-aid/summer-aid">
          Financial Aid website</a>. Please visit the <a href="https://extended.humboldt.edu/extended-education/summer-session">Summer 2024 website</a> for more information.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>Go Jacks! <br><br>
          Cindy Bumgarner, EdD <br>
          Dean, College of Extended Education & Global Engagement
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
